title._content: Finalists in bathing beauties competition, Luna Park, Sydney, 1937 by Sam Hood

description._content: Another photograph from the series reproduced The Labor Daily, 3/5/1937. Sydney Exposures exhibition caption: Bathing beauties, Milsons Point, 1 May 1937 : Some of the finalists in the 1937 Sydney's Bathing Beauty contest try the big dipper at Luna Park, where judging took place. With a &50 first prize, there was no lack of entrants. The winner was Doreen Lansley of Hurlstone Park.
